item.title: [BEAM-8979] protoc-gen-mypy: program not found or is not executable
item.description:
In some tests, `:sdks:python:sdist:` task fails due to problems in finding protoc-gen-mypy. The following tests are affected (there might be more):

  • https://builds.apache.org/job/beam_LoadTests_Python_37_ParDo_Dataflow_Batch_PR/
  • https://builds.apache.org/job/beam_BiqQueryIO_Write_Performance_Test_Python_Batch/

Relevant logs:

This is what I have tried so far to resolve this (without being successful):

  • Including --plugin=protoc-gen-mypy={abs_path_to_executable} parameter to the protoc call ingen_protos.py:131
  • Appending protoc-gen-mypy's directory to the PATH variable

I wasn't able to reproduce this error locally.

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: https://github.com/apache/beam/pull/10400 was merged and the tests are now working. I'll leave this issue unresolved, so that we would remember about it when bringing back mypy-protobuf

to install mypy-protobuf.

Could the changes in https://github.com/apache/beam/pull/10038 automate this step when running setup.py or tox?

This would be resolved if appropriate PATH and PYTHONPATH are set when using protoc-gen-mypy and futurize within gen_protos.py.
If chadrik is not working on now, I'll do on this.
How about you?
I thought this issue was resolved. Can you provide the error you are getting and how to reproduce it? What version of beam are you using?
